Héctor "Hetin" Reyes: "Basketball was my life"
The world stroller of the basketball, Héctor "Hetin" Reyes, was longer to the wicker sport than 60 years linkedly and has travelled around the whole world.
A few in Puerto Rico dispose of such a big spiritual collection of the history of the basketball of the country like Héctor "Hetin" Reyes.
Before he was bound by a stroke in 2008 to the wheel chair, Rexes was during 6 years a part of this sport, it is as a player of lower classes, players of the first national league, authorised representatives and leaders in the BSN with the Vaqueros de Bayamón or president of the basketball association.
"All my life I have put on in the basketball many hats, even several at the same time when I was a president of the BSN, general managers of the national team and president of the association in the 90s" remembered Reyes in a visit of Primera Hora with him at home in Bayamón where he lives with Isabel, his faithful wife for more than 50 years.
"Basketball was my life."
Reyes does not exaggerate with this statement.
The walls of his house are decorated almost everybody with photos and recollections of his long career and testify them.
Bayamón in the heart
The most emotional recollections are that which remind of his time with the Vaqueros from the middle of the 50s as a player till 1982 where he celebrated his 15-year-old jubilee as a comanager or manager of the club.
"This was my prime of life which I have enjoyed mostly because I part of eight masteries of the Vaqueros since 1967 am it as a manager, comanager or trainer might be.
These were many fulfilling years, including five masteries successively from 1971 to 1975.
And then I said goodbye with a mastery in 1981, the year of the debut to Jerome Mincy with BSN.
From then took over "Cuco" Ortiz who was a very good governor", says Reyes.
I still know that Bartow which worked here as a trainer and was done at the university of Alabama (Birmingham) said me genes: "I have very much a strong and 2-m-player.
